cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.IT, cs.DS, cs.CC 

This paper is primarily focused on the expressibility of neural networks, which is a core topic in machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the architecture of neural networks, which is related to optimization and training, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) another likely category. The paper also involves mathematical analysis, which could fall under cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper discusses the growth of neuron requirements, which could be related to cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
